m_q.target_metric: Count of NIFC Geographic Areas that each US state falls into
sub_questions: What are the full names of US states?
Which NIFC Geographic Areas does each state intersect with?
What is the count of geographic areas per state?
Which state(s) have the maximum count?

schema_conflicts: No common non-spatial keys for joining

scale_issues: Geometry data may be in different coordinate reference systems
NIFC geographic areas may overlap state boundaries
cross_source_conflicts: Coordinate reference system alignment needed for spatial join
State boundaries may not align perfectly with NIFC geographic area boundaries

format_notes: Both files are GeoPackage format with geometry columns
usa.gpkg contains administrative boundaries at multiple levels (adm0, adm1, adm2)
nifc_geographic_areas.gpkg contains NIFC Geographic Area Coordination Center boundaries
Spatial operations required for intersection analysis

constraints: Only include adm1 (state) level records from usa.gpkg
Count distinct NIFC Geographic Areas per state
Output must use full state names from adm1_name column
derived_filters: Filter usa.gpkg to state-level administrative units (adm1)
Ensure records represent US states, not territories or other subdivisions
Remove duplicate state-area intersections if any
statistical_tests: Maximum count of geographic areas per state
Distribution of geographic area counts across states
output_format_requirements: Return full state names (adm1_name), not abbreviations
Include count of NIFC Geographic Areas per state
Results should list states falling into the most geographic areas
